*Initialize a git repository with no work folder :

git init --bare

---------

*List all remotes plus details :

git remote -v

---------

*Add remote :

git add <remote_name> <URI_to_repository>

---------

*Rename a remote :

git remote rename <old_name> <new_name>

---------

*List remote available branches :

git branch -r

---------

*Push to remote branch:

git push <remote_name> <remote_branch>

--------- 

*Delete a remote branch :

git push <remote_name> --delete <remote_branch>

---------

*Pull commits from remote branch :

git pull <remote_name> <branch_name> 

---------

*Clone a remote repository :

git clone <URI>

*Clone a remote repository but only get a limited history :

git clone <URI> --depth <depth_integer_value>

---------

*If local branch is behind remote branch, a pull with rebase can fix it (not like merge which requires an additional commit):

git pull --rebase <remote_name> <remote_branch_name>

---------

*To activate automatic rebase pull (git pull --rebase) :

gti config --global branch.autosetuprebase always















